---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About" description="About Mike Murphy and the work behind mikemurphy.ai." canonical="/about/">
  <main class="mm-container grid gap-12 py-16 lg:grid-cols-[24rem_1fr] lg:items-start">
    <aside class="mx-auto w-full max-w-sm lg:order-none">
      <div class="mm-polaroid -rotate-2">
        <div class="mm-polaroid-photo">
          <img src="/assets/brand/avatar-mike-orange-1200.png" alt="Mike Murphy" />
        </div>
        <p>Mike</p>
      </div>
    </aside>
    <section>
      <p class="mm-eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1 class="mm-h1 mt-3">Hi, I'm Mike Murphy.</h1>
      <p class="mm-lede mt-5">
        I make practical tutorials for people who want to use AI tools, automation, and creative tech without turning every project into a giant mystery.
      </p>
      <div class="mm-prose prose mt-8">
        <p>
          Tutorials are the flagship here because teaching is the clearest way to turn curiosity into something useful. AI Unplugged is the weekly pulse: what I am trying, what is working, and what feels worth remembering.
        </p>
        <p>
          This site is my AI knowledge hub and workshop notebook. On the surface it is a website. Under the hood, it is becoming the machine I use to build, publish, learn, and share what survives real use.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
        <a href="/tutorials/" class="mm-button">Browse tutorials</a>
        <a href="/contact/" class="mm-button mm-button-secondary">Get in touch</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
